        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Enforce repair contract before checkpointing",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nEnforce the repair contract before creating checkpoint commits.\n\nThe executor now checks the real changed-file set against the fix artifact's likely files / validation-derived contract before checkpointing. This catches repairs that touch no relevant files or only unrelated lockfiles.\n\n## Scope\n\nModel-agnostic ClawSweeper executor behavior only. No model backend, OpenAI-compatible, adapter, provider-specific code, or review/result normalization.\n\n## Validation evidence\n\n```text\ncorepack pnpm run build:repair\nnode --test test/repair/execute-fix-artifact-source.test.ts\n```\n\nResult:\n\n```text\nbuild:repair: passed\nexecute-fix-artifact-source.test.ts: 7/7 tests passed\n```\n\nThe new regression covers:\n\n```text\nrepair contract enforces likely file touch before checkpointing\n```\n\nIt also verifies the git porcelain path parser uses `line.slice(3)` instead of trimming before offset parsing.\n",
